						<summary>

						<p>On a fragment of a stone lying in the Śaṅkaraliṅga temple.</p>						

						<p>Siṅghaṇa, 1208 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated the 9th regnal year of the king, Vibhava, Āshāḍha śu. 15, Monday, Saṅkramaṇa. In the cyclic year Vibhava corresponding to 1208 A.D., the details correspond to June 30, the <hi rend="italic">tithi,</hi> however, being ba. 1. The Saṅkramaṇa occurred on June 26, Thursday.</p>						

						<p>It mentions Ayyāvaḷe Five Hundred <hi rend="italic">Svāmis</hi> and Bimmarasa. The god Sōmanātha is referred to. The epigraph is fragmentary and worn out.</p>						

						</summary>
